        <section class="intro margins">
            <h5>
                Being part of a community means cooperating and belonging with different perspectives and backgrounds. Holding respectful conversations with those who disagree can be uncomfortable, but Michael and Emily believe that exploring history opens people up to ideas that help find common&nbsp;ground.
